    • Class backbone.Layer extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      3954124190863354091L

      • Serialized Fields

        • myString

          java.lang.String myString
          String representation of layer. Defaultly the memory address, but when instantiated changes to filename

        • red

          double red
          The amount of red being shown 1 indicates that all the red is being shown while 0 indicates no red is being shown

        • green

          double green
          The amount of green being shown 1 indicates that all the green is being shown while 0 indicates no green is being shown

        • blue

          double blue
          The amount of blue being shown 1 indicates that all the blue is being shown while 0 indicates no blue is being shown

        • overall

          double overall
          The brightness being shown 1 indicates that the image is at full brightness while 0 indicates no brightness

        • contrast

          double contrast
          The amount of contrast in the image 0 represents the amount of contrast being shown regularly, 1 represents no contrast, and a negative number indicates increased contrast over the initial image.

        • grayscale

          boolean grayscale
          A boolean representing whether or not the image should be grayscaled.

        • inverted

          boolean inverted
          A boolean representing whether or not the colors of the image should be inverted

        • invertedalpha

          boolean invertedalpha
          A boolean representing whether or not the alpha channel of the image should be inverted

        • updates

          boolean[] updates
          A boolean array which determines for each thread updating the image of whether or not to run.

        • redarray

          short[][] redarray
          A short matrix containing the red color values for the original image. The first argument represents width or "x" while the second represents height or "y".

        • greenarray

          short[][] greenarray
          A short matrix containing the green color values for the original image. The first argument represents width or "x" while the second represents height or "y".

        • bluearray

          short[][] bluearray
          A short matrix containing the blue color values for the original image. The first argument represents width or "x" while the second represents height or "y".

        • alphaarray

          short[][] alphaarray
          A short matrix containing the alpha color values for the both the original and filtered images. The first argument represents width or "x" while the second represents height or "y".

        • filteredRed

          short[][] filteredRed
          A short matrix containing the red color values for the filtered image. The first argument represents width or "x" while the second represents height or "y".

        • filteredGreen

          short[][] filteredGreen
          A short matrix containing the green color values for the filtered image. The first argument represents width or "x" while the second represents height or "y".

        • filteredBlue

          short[][] filteredBlue
          A short matrix containing the blue color values for the filtered image. The first argument represents width or "x" while the second represents height or "y".

        • x

          double x
          The leftmost coordinate of the image. The bounds are from [0, 1]

        • y

          double y
          The topmost coordinate of the image. The bounds are from [0, 1]

        • xsize

          double xsize
          The width of the image. A size of 1 indicates that if centered, it would occupy the entire image.

        • ysize

          double ysize
          The height of the image. A size of 1 indicates that if centered, it would occupy the entire image.

        • filtered

          java.awt.image.BufferedImage filtered
          The filtered image

        • exchange

          double exchange
          The correspondance between a change in the slider and the textfield/value 1 means that each change will be the same 10 means that for every 10 changes in the slider, the textfield/value will move once

        • shift

          double shift
          The shift between the the textfield/value and the slider 0 indicates no shift 10 indicates that the slider will be 10 less than the textField
